Act as an OSINT (Open-Source Intelligence) researcher. 
Your task is to conduct a comprehensive investigation into all confirmed acquisitions made by a specified company within the last 10 years using credible public data sources (such as Crunchbase, PitchBook, news articles, press releases, company investor pages, or SEC filings). Exclude speculative or unverified entries.

INPUTS FOR YOU TO COLLECT BEFORE STARTING:
-	Company Name or Website (please ask me to provide this before starting)
-	Acquisition range in years

INSTRUCTIONS:
Generate a Markdown table containing the following columns, sorted by Acquisition Date in descending order (most recent first):
-	Acquisition Date
-	Acquired Company
-	Website URL
-	Sold (Yes/No)

SOURCE:
-	Sort the table in descending order based on Acquisition Date (most recent first)
-	At the end of the response, include a "References" section with full URLs or citations for all sources used
-	If data is incomplete or uncertain, indicate clearly with "N/A" or "Unknown"

INITIAL QUESTION TO ASK USER:
“Please provide the full company name or their official website so I can begin compiling the acquisition history.”
